    <text>
        <body>
            <p>
                <lg type="poem">
                    <pb facs="Wordsworth_1798_133.png"/>
                    <head type="main" rend="centre uppercase font-size(3mm)">
                        LINES</head>
                    <head type="sub" rend="centre uppercase font-size(1.5mm)">
                        WRITTEN IN EARLY SPRING.
                    </head>
                        <figure type="double-line" rend="length(15mm)"/>
             
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>I heard a thousand blended notes,</l>
                        <l>While in a grove I sate reclined,</l>
                        <l>In that sweet mood when pleasant thoughts</l>
                        <l>Bring sad thoughts to the mind.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>To her fair works did nature link</l>
                        <l>The human soul that through me ran ;</l>
                        <l>And much it griev’d my heart to think</l>
                        <l>What man has made of man.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <pb facs="Wordsworth_1798_134.png" n="116"/>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>Through primrose-tufts, in that sweet bower,</l>
                        <l>The periwinkle trail’d is wreathes ;</l>
                        <l>And ’tis my faith that every flower</l>
                        <l>Enjoys the air it breathes.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>The birds around me hopp’d and play’d :</l>
                        <l>Their thoughts I cannot measure,</l>
                        <l>But the least motion which they made,</l>
                        <l>It seem’d a thrill of pleasure.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>The budding twigs spread out their fan,</l>
                        <l>To catch the breezy air ;</l>
                        <l>And I must think, do all I can,</l>
                        <l>That there was pleasure there.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>If I these thoughts may not prevent,</l>
                        <l>If such be of my creed the plan,</l>
                        <l>Have I not reason to lament</l>
                        <l>What man has made of man ?</l>
                    </lg>
                </lg>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
